            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 170,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "52e96f4918ed43308370f4576b59947c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Agile",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "The multiple attack penalty you take with this weapon on the second attack on your turn is \u20134 instead of \u20135, and \u20138 instead of \u201310 on the third and subsequent attacks in the turn.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 179,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6a57956799f3d30121d529e48f12904c",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Finesse",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 282",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 282,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls using this melee weapon. You still calculate damage using Strength.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 196,
